solution.p:
The Poiseuille's law says that

	Q = \frac{\pi R^4}{8\eta L} \Delta p.

Therefore,

	R = \left( \frac{8\eta L}{\pi \Delta p}\  Q\right )^{1/4}.

In this problem, various given quantities should be first converted into the same system of units. We will convert them into standard SI system.

	 \amp Q = 1 \frac{\text{L}}{\text{Day}} = \frac{10^{-3}\ \text{m}^3}{24\times 3600\ \text{s}} =  0.01157 \ \text{m}^3\text{s}
	 \amp \Delta p = 0.5\ \text{atm} = 2.53\times 10^{4}\ \text{Pa} 
	 \amp L = 0.05\ \text{m} 
	 \amp \eta = 2.7\ \text{cP} = 2.7\times 10^{-3}\ \text{Pa.s} 

Therefore,  R = 112\, \mu\text{m}.  The diameter of the vein would be 224\, \mu\text{m}.

Therefore,

	 \Delta p \amp = \dfrac{8}{\pi} \frac{\eta L}{R^4} 
	 \amp = \dfrac{8}{\pi} \frac{1.002 \times 10^{-3} \times 2.54\times 10^{-2}}{  (1.5\times 10^{-4})^4} 
	 \amp = 8885\text{ Pa}

This gives pressure at the back end of the needle

	p_{\text{high}} = p_{\text{vein}} + \Delta p = 1.026 \times 10^{5}  + 8885  = 111485\text{ Pa}.

We convert this to  \text{mm Hg}.

	111485\text{ Pa} = 111485\times \dfrac{760}{1.013\times 10^{5}} = 836\text{ mm Hg}.
